{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place lemon zest and sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>8 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and beat <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and beat <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and beat <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add vanilla and egg and mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>.","Add flour and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then mix <b>15 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer dough onto a well-floured silicone bread mat or work surface and divide into 2 even portions. Shape each portion into a disc, then wrap in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for 1-2 hours or until firm enough to roll (see Tips).","Preheat oven to 170°C. Line 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Working quickly, with one batch at a time, transfer dough onto a well-floured silicone bread mat or work surface and roll out to 5 mm thickness (see Tips). Cut into desired shapes and transfer onto prepared baking trays. Repeat rolling and cutting until all dough has been used. Bake for 8-10 minutes (170°C) or until lightly golden. Allow to cool on baking trays for 10 minutes, then transfer onto wire racks to cool completely. Once cool, decorate biscuits as desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 pieces lemon zest (1 x 4 cm), no white pith","130 g sugar","220 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces and softened","2 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 egg","350 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting"]}],"id":"r138793","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-YXTKidoaLFw\/XZWqtmkoMgI\/AAAAAAAAfcI\/52OWT4MAjjoMme4DuM5ZvODcLyrUuSh5QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_T6deRMDONp1BpaT5.png","title":"Simple butter biscuits","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0.8 g","fat":"3.2 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"6.2 g","calories":"237 kJ \/ 56 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, 2 baking trays (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, rolling pin, cookie cutter, wire rack, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To freeze biscuit dough, place into freezer instead of refrigerator after wrapping in plastic wrap. Remove from freezer 1-2 hours before rolling. You may need a little extra flour when rolling. Dough can be frozen for up to 1 month.","When rolling out the dough, flour your work surface well; as you roll, lift and rotate your dough to prevent sticking.","<strong>Gluten free simple butter biscuits: <\/strong>For a gluten free biscuit substitute plain flour with 350 g gluten free plain flour.<strong><br><\/strong>"],"basicInfo":["easy","50m","3h 20m","60 portions"]}